<node id="World Athletics Federation">
  <data key="d0">World Athletics Federation</data>
  <data key="d1">organization</data>
  <data key="d2">World Athletics Federation, also known as World Athletics, is the global governing body for athletics. It plays a pivotal role in organizing the World Athletics Championships, which are held biennially and feature a wide range of track and field events. The federation is responsible for validating world records in athletics, ensuring that all performances meet the required standards and criteria. This includes verifying the authenticity of records set during competitions and maintaining an official list of recognized world records.

The World Athletics Federation oversees the World Athletics Championship, which is a significant event under its purview. It also handles record validations, ensuring that all athletic achievements are accurately documented and verified. The federation's responsibilities extend to setting rules and regulations for the sport, as well as supporting athletes through various programs and initiatives aimed at fostering the growth and development of athletics worldwide. These efforts make World Athletics a crucial organization in the realm of track and field sports.&lt;SEP&gt;The World Athletics Federation is the governing body overseeing the World Athletics Championship and record validations.&lt;SEP&gt;The World Athletics Federation is the governing body overseeing the World Athletics Championship and record validations.&lt;SEP&gt;The World Athletics Federation is the governing body overseeing the World Athletics Championship and record validations.</data>
